[2] Sudan
Date: Thu 2 Apr 2015
Source: StarAfrica, APA report [abridged & edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/sudan-unicef-launches-measles-vaccination-campaign-after-outbreak.html


Sudan: UNICEF launches measles vaccination campaign after outbreak
------------------------------------------------------------------
The United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) will launch a wide measles agency said in a statement on Thursday [2 Apr 2015]. UNICEF has confirmed in the statement that it has ordered 9.6 million doses of measles vaccines to support the Sudanese Ministry of Health in combating the current measles outbreak in the country.

The UN Children's Rights and Emergency Relief Organization will conduct a mass immunization campaign, in cooperation with the Health Ministry targeting 7.9 million children from 9 months to 15 years in 26 affected and 70 high-risk localities. According to UNICEF, the 1st batch of more than 2 million doses arrived at Khartoum National Airport on Tuesday [31 Mar 2015].

During the past 3 months, measles has spread across 29 localities in 16 of Sudan's 18 states. By 26 Mar 2015, confirmed measles cases numbered 1120. The most affected state is Kassala (353 cases, 2 deaths) followed by Red Sea (205 cases and 3 deaths), and North Darfur (140 cases, 12 deaths), according to UNICEF.

