[4] Germany (Berlin)
Date: Sat 4 April 2015
Source: The SundayNews [summ., edited]
http://www.thesundaily.my/news/1374414


Almost 1000 cases of measles reported in Berlin
-----------------------------------------------
Since the start of an outbreak of measles in the German capital in October [2014], there have been almost 1000 cases of the highly contagious disease, Berlin's health authorities reported this week [week ending 4 Apr 2015]. Of the 970 cases reported by Thursday [2 Apr 2015], 849 have been reported since January [2015], the Berlin State Office for Health and Social Affair said.

Around a quarter of cases are so severe they need to be treated in hospital. Measles attacks the immune system and can lead to serious infections of the lungs or brain. The outbreak, one of the worst in Germany in a decade, does not appear to be slowing, the authorities said.

The reasons behind the severity of the Berlin outbreak is a lack of knowledge in the population and too many young people who were not vaccinated against the disease over unfounded fears about the side effects of the vaccine.

Berlin Health Senator Mario Czaja urged parents and children who were not vaccinated to go to the doctor and get immunized against the disease.

