[5] Canada (British Columbia)
Date: Thu 2 Apr 2015
Source: Radio Canada [in French, transl., edited]
http://ici.radio-canada.ca/regions/colombie-britannique/2015/04/02/002-rougeole-maladie-vancouver.shtml


Four confirmed cases of measles in Metro Vancouver
--------------------------------------------------
Two new cases of measles have been confirmed in Metro Vancouver [British Columbia province] by public health authorities. The total number of recent infections in the region now stands at 4 cases.

According to the Vancouver Coastal Health Authority, a student of the Christian school Carver Christian High School in Burnaby is a new case. He was aboard a flight of Air China that landed in Vancouver on 21 Mar 2015, with 2 other passengers who were suffering from the disease.

Governance of Fraser Health organized a vaccination clinic Thursday [2 Apr 2015] at Carver Christian High School. According to Dr. Michelle Murti of governance, the incubation period for measles can extend up to 3 weeks, which means that there could be other cases that have not yet been diagnosed.

"People can have a little fever, cough and runny nose, and it's only a few days later that the typical measles rash appears," she says.

The Public Health Agency of Canada points out that anyone who is not immunized against measles can contract the disease, and that children are particularly vulnerable.

