[7] USA (Florida)
Date: Tue 31 Mar 2015
Source: Vaccine News Daily [edited]
http://vaccinenewsdaily.com/news/333260-florida-confirms-measles-case/


Florida confirms measles case
-----------------------------
The Florida Department of Health recently confirmed that an international traveler who visited the state had the measles. The traveler attended an international conference on 16 and 17 Mar 2015 at the Gaylord Palms Resort and Convention Center in Kissimmee, Florida. The individual's travel history included several counties in central and south Florida, including Osceola, Orange, Miami-Dade and Sarasota counties between 14 and 20 Mar 2015. The traveler did not spend any time at amusement parks. He was hospitalized for his illness from 20 to 24 Mar 2015, and flew out of Florida on 25 Mar 2015.

All of the people who attended the international conference have been notified of the situation. Symptoms of measles include a fever; cough; blotchy rash; feeling run down or achy; and having a runny nose, red, watery eyes, and tiny white spots with bluish-white centers inside the mouth. Symptoms appear 7 to 14 days after exposure.

Health professionals in Florida and the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention encourage the general public to receive the Measles Mumps and Rubella (MMR) vaccine to prevent contracting the disease. This vaccine requires multiple doses; one dose is not enough to guarantee protection from the virus.

